# Getting Started

Welcome! This guide will help you set up CSA Admin and get [your registration form](<%= new_members_member_url(subdomain: Current.org.members_subdomain) %>) ready to welcome new members. Let's get started!

## 1. Invite Other Admins {#inviting-other-admins}

Setting up your organization is easier as a team! You can [invite other admins](/admins/new) right away. An email will be sent to them so they can connect and join you.

[Specific access permissions](/permissions) can be configured if needed.

## 2. Deliveries {#deliveries}

Start by [creating your delivery dates](/deliveries) for the upcoming fiscal year. The number of deliveries determines the price of memberships, so they're required before you can create anything else.

[A handbook page](/handbook/deliveries) is available with more details, including a section on [delivery cycles](/handbook/deliveries#delivery-cycles).

> Don't worry if the exact dates aren't finalized yet. Just make sure you have the right number of deliveries so that prices are correct on the registration form. You can always adjust the dates later.

## 3. Basket Sizes {#basket-sizes}

Next, [create your basket sizes](/basket_sizes) (e.g. small, large). These define the types of memberships your members can choose from.

## 4. Basket Complements (optional) {#basket-complements}

[Basket complements](/basket_complements) are optional add-ons like bread, cheese, or eggs that members can subscribe to alongside their basket. Each complement can be delivered on specific deliveries, for example only during the winter period or every other week.

## 5. Depots {#depots}

[Create at least one depot](/depots), the pickup locations where members collect their baskets.

A price can also be set per depot to cover extra preparation or delivery costs. It will be automatically included when billing memberships.

## 6. Registration Form {#registration-form}

Now that your deliveries, basket sizes, and depots are configured, your [registration form](<%= new_members_member_url(subdomain: Current.org.members_subdomain) %>) should be taking shape and soon be ready to welcome new members!

Check out the [registration form handbook page](/handbook/registration) to learn how each setting affects the form and find tips on fine-tuning it.

## 7. Billing & Payments {#billing-payments}

<!-- country:CH -->
To generate QR-invoices, you need a [QR-IBAN](/handbook/billing#qr-iban) from your bank. This is different from your regular IBAN and is required for Swiss QR-invoices with reference numbers. Request one from your bank as soon as possible and enter it in [your billing settings](/settings#billing).
<!-- /country:CH -->

<!-- country:!CH -->
To generate invoices, make sure to enter your IBAN in [your billing settings](/settings#billing). If you use [SEPA direct debit](/handbook/billing#sepa), you'll also need to configure your creditor identifier there.
<!-- /country:!CH -->

For automatic payment import, you'll want to [set up an EBICS connection](/handbook/billing#ebics-setup) with your bank. This process takes a few days, so it's worth starting early. In the meantime, you can [manually import](/handbook/billing#manual-import) payment files from your e-banking.

For more details on all billing-related topics, check out the [billing handbook page](/handbook/billing).

---

That's it for the essentials! The rest you can discover as you go. Each section of the [handbook](/handbook) covers a specific topic in detail. If you have any questions, don't hesitate to [contact me](/support). Happy setting up! 🙌🏻
